# Charoda, Republic of Dagestan

}}
Charoda () is a rural locality (a selo) in Charodinsky District, Republic of Dagestan, Russia. Population:  There is 1 street in this selo.
Geography
Selo is located 5&nbsp;km from Tsurib (the district's administrative centre), 96&nbsp;km from Makhachkala (capital of Dagestan) and 1,678&nbsp;km from Moscow. Murukh is the nearest rural locality.
